- 5,781sqm* site in Hume with rear exposure to Monaro Highway
- 1,660sqm* stand alone building with parking and drive around hardstand
- Building comprises showroom, offices, amenities, workshops, storage and wash bay
- Leased to Westrac on a NET lease expiring 31 December 2015.
- Current net income: $218,103pa*

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 20 March 2014

On behalf of Matt Adams & Nathan Landrey receivers and managers of Kenoss Pty. Ltd (Administrators Appointed)

* (approx)

Hume is an expanding industrial suburb located some 15km south of CanberraAƒÂ¢A‚a‚Â¬A‚a„Â¢s CBD adjacent to the Monaro Highway. The property is located approximately half way down Sheppard Street which is the main thoroughfare through the estate.

62 Sheppard Street is a flat regular shaped block with frontage to Sheppard Street. Constructed on the block is a single storey metal clad industrial warehouse of steel frame, concrete slab flooring and metal deck roof.

The rear area is available for lease. The area comprises approx 470sqm of warehouse with amenities including shower, toilets and kitchenette. The warehouse also comprises 3 phase power supply, alarm system and clearance heights between 5.3m and 7.8m.

The warehouse is also serviced by an exclusive yard area measuring approx 1,000sqm with 2.4m high perimeter fencing and gated access to the front. There is also a triple interceptor installed on site for the use of a wash bay.

470sqm Warehouse @ $100/sqm = $47,000pa
1000sqm Yard Area @ $20/sqm = $20,000pa
= Total Asking Rent = $67,000pa +GST
